summary: Captain Marvel highlights why we need more female leads in action movies.
body:
Captain Marvel highlights why we need more female leads in action movies.

  1. Captain Marvel is Marvel’s first female led superhero film. It’s 2019. They’ve been making movies for 25 years. This isn’t talked about enough.
  2. When I told my dad that I was excited to see Captain Marvel because of the above, he was confused because he was wondering why the movie was named after a man then. He heard Captain and thought man. He heard Marvel and thought man. EDIT: I have been informed that there was a male Captain Marvel before the movie, obviously I had never heard of him before, and when I googled Captain Marvel, only pictures of the female one and Captain America came up, sorry for the confusion.
  3. I’ve always loved avengers, but there was never even one I could relate to except Black Widow, who is yet to have her own movie. I would have KILLED for Captain Marvel when I was a kid.
  4. Brie Larson fucking owns me.

body:
